article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 77, Loyola of Chicago 68
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- James Eayrs scored 20 points and Ricky Franklin 18 Tuesday night as Wisconsin-Milwaukee defeated Loyola of Chicago 77-68 in the first round of the Horizon League tournament. Milwaukee (17-13, 12-7) plays Wright State Friday in a second-round game in Indianapolis. Milwaukee's victory was revenge against the team that defeated it in first-round games the last two seasons. The Ramblers (14-18, 6-13) were led by J.R. Blount, who scored all but two of his 20 points in the second half, and Jordan Hicks who also had 20. Walt Gibler added 14. Milwaukee led 35-17 at halftime and made it 44-19 early in the second half on a Deonte Roberts basket. The Ramblers battled back to within seven points four times late in the game but could get no closer.
